Rebel fighters in Syria are developing their own hand-made weapons as they battle the government regime.

Fighters from the Suqour al-Sham Brigade are setting up weapons factories in caves to make shells and rockets as they take on the might of President Bashar Al-Assad's regime.

These pictures show men developing mortar shells from gas canisters and making their own rockets using welding materials. 

