Yesterday, two car bombs killed at least 25 people and wounded another 80 celebrating the new year festival of Nowruz in the mainly Kurdish city of Hassaka in northeastern Syria, according to state media.

The Syrian Observatory for Human Rights group, which tracks the four-year-old Syrian civil war, said 33 people, including children, were killed in the attack which it said was carried out by Islamic State.

 

 

